title: PPPP’s  Jam Khan Shoro wins PS- 60 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP), Jam Khan Shoro has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-60, Hyderabad-1 , by securing 37,538 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Ayaz Latif Paligo of Grand Democratic Alliance (GDA) who bagged 6,922 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 38.76 %.
